Description: Fix CVE-2026-61863 memory leak in TIFF encoder (WriteGROUP4Image)
 In coders/tiff.c, WriteGROUP4Image throws UnableToCreateTemporaryFile
 when a temporary file cannot be created (AcquireUniqueFileResource /
 fdopen failure) without first releasing the huffman_image object,
 leaking that Image structure (CWE-401). This adds the missing
 huffman_image=DestroyImage(huffman_image) call before the exception is
 thrown, matching the existing cleanup pattern used elsewhere in the
 same function.
Origin: upstream, commit:f3ff3afee942a19e3041568bfa740d48213a3dec
Bug: https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick/security/advisories/GHSA-6vxp-gfwf-hcr9
Author: Cristy <urban-warrior@imagemagick.org>
Last-Update: 2026-07-17

--- a/coders/tiff.c
+++ b/coders/tiff.c
@@ -2543,6 +2543,7 @@ static MagickBooleanType WriteGROUP4Imag
     file=fdopen(unique_file,"wb");
   if ((unique_file == -1) || (file == (FILE *) NULL))
     {
+      huffman_image=DestroyImage(huffman_image);
       ThrowFileException(&image->exception,FileOpenError,
         "UnableToCreateTemporaryFile",filename);
       return(MagickFalse);
Description: CVE-2026-61866 - fix memory leak in JNG encoder when blob cannot be opened
 In coders/png.c the JNG encoder's WriteOneJNGImage() throws a memory
 allocation error via ThrowWriterException when OpenBlob() fails, without
 first destroying the already-allocated jpeg_image / jpeg_image_info
 structures, leaking memory (CWE-401). This adds DestroyImage and
 DestroyImageInfo cleanup before the exception is thrown.
Origin: upstream, commit:353e2604d1983b6d8ec4c04f4f38bbd4668ba0e1
Author: Cristy <urban-warrior@imagemagick.org>
Last-Update: 2026-07-17

--- a/coders/png.c
+++ b/coders/png.c
@@ -12752,7 +12752,11 @@ static MagickBooleanType WriteOneJNGImage(MngInfo *mng_info,
             &image->exception);
 
           if (status == MagickFalse)
-            ThrowWriterException(ResourceLimitError,"MemoryAllocationFailed");
+            {
+              jpeg_image=DestroyImage(jpeg_image);
+              jpeg_image_info=DestroyImageInfo(jpeg_image_info);
+              ThrowWriterException(ResourceLimitError,"MemoryAllocationFailed");
+            }
 
           (void) CopyMagickString(jpeg_image_info->magick,"JPEG",MaxTextExtent);
           (void) CopyMagickString(jpeg_image->magick,"JPEG",MaxTextExtent);
Description: Fix CVE-2026-56362 heap-buffer-overflow read in GetPixelIndex
 OpenPixelCache updated image channel metadata before pixel cache memory
 allocation. When both memory and disk allocation attempts fail in
 PersistPixelCache, the cache_info->type was left in a state that could
 cause a heap-buffer-overflow read in writers that call GetPixelIndex.
 Reset cache_info->type to UndefinedCache when the DiskResource acquire
 fails so subsequent readers do not consume the stale cache layout.
Origin: upstream, commit:67778a697216aa2bfc2ccfd2f0282c04c7b4872e
Author: Cristy <urban-warrior@imagemagick.org>
Bug: https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick6/commit/67778a697216aa2bfc2ccfd2f0282c04c7b4872e
Last-Update: 2026-07-20
---
--- a/magick/cache.c
+++ b/magick/cache.c
@@ -4317,6 +4317,7 @@ MagickExport MagickBooleanType PersistPi
   status=AcquireMagickResource(DiskResource,cache_info->length);
   if (status == MagickFalse)
     {
+      cache_info->type=UndefinedCache;
       (void) ThrowMagickException(exception,GetMagickModule(),CacheError,
         "CacheResourcesExhausted","`%s'",image->filename);
       return(MagickFalse);
